Collar: short, reaches the base of the radioles, not incised ventrally or laterally. Collar with hooded (limbate) chaetae of two sizes (
Figs 3F–G
).

Abdomen: with short achaetiger region followed by 66 (n=4, r:(7)51–77, µ=62±11.9) chaetigers. Anterior and middle chaetigers with almost straight geniculate chaetae (
Figs 3J–K
). Posterior chaetigers with “capillary” chaetae. Uncini saw-shaped, with two rows of teeth (
Figs 3N–O
), 5–6 teeth in lateral view. Abdomen with two terminal anal cirri.
